<subSubSection id="374BBF8D16D6166495A69903360470C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="029C6C1582C123C086D0401A158F7656" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="69A29B76133FCAA2271B61F5DC16318E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This new variety differs from the other varieties (
<taxonomicName id="0D9CF72E05975AC8761971012CDB0D41" authority="Jacq. var. monogyna" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Crataegus monogyna var. monogyna" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="monogyna" variety="monogyna">Crataegus monogyna Jacq. var. monogyna</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D8BA3B003E1A98380D7097CBB6107925" authorityName="K. I. Chr" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Lange" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Crataegus monogyna var. lasiocarpa" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="monogyna" variety="lasiocarpa">Crataegus monogyna var. lasiocarpa</taxonomicName>
(Lange) K.I.Christ.) sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="A17A941E874A109F7D5C384601A8B657" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027810" author="Christensen, KI" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Christensen, KI, 1992. Revision of Crataegussect.Crataegus and nothosect. Crataeguineae (Rosaceae-Maloideae) in the Old World. Systematic Botany Monographs: 35. https://doi.org/10.2307/25027810" title="Revision of Crataegussect. Crataegus and nothosect. Crataeguineae (Rosaceae-Maloideae) in the Old World. Systematic Botany Monographs: 35." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027810" year="1992">Christensen (1992)</bibRefCitation>
by its orange fruit colour in contrast to red fruits in the former.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
